            <note anchored="true">
               In detail: 
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sperber (1984) 34-35</bibl>.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 42a</bibl>,
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 21b</bibl>, distinguish between 1. buying and 2. bill of sale.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 28b</bibl> traces back to Hebr. <term xml:lang="jpa">אונה</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾwnh</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">ʾonah</term> 'possession, title of possession, deed', writing: “The phonetic coincidence with <term xml:lang="grc">ὠνή</term> produced the peculiar use of our w. in connection with Greek terms, in the Palest. literature.”
   </note>
